The '''Sicilian National Movement''' ({{lang-it|Movimento Nazionale Siciliano}}, '''MNS''') is a [[separatism|separatist]] coalition of parties active in [[Sicily]].
The coalition was launced in November 2016<ref>http://www.movimentonazionalesiciliano.eu/manifesto</ref> and officially founded in January 2017. Its three founding members were: [[Sicily Nation]] (SN), the [[Sicilian Independence Movement]] (MIS; re-edition of the separatist party which was active after [[World War II]]) and the [[Sicilian National Front]] (FNS).<ref>http://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/politica/12279089/sicilia-nasce-il-movimento-nazionale-siciliano-e-candida-alla-regione-gaetano-armao.html</ref>
Since its foundation, the MNS supported [[Gaetano Armao]], SN leader, for [[President of Sicily]] in the [[Sicilian regional election, 2017|2017 regional election]].<ref>http://palermo.repubblica.it/dettaglio-news/-/4681510</ref><ref>http://www.secoloditalia.it/2017/02/gli-autonomisti-siciliani-contro-crocetta-e-orlando-affossano-lisola</ref>
In the summer of 2017 Armao, with the support of the MNS,<ref>http://www.movimentonazionalesiciliano.eu/sicilianisti-armao-sicilianindignati</ref> launched a broader '''Union of Indignant Sicilians''' (''Unione dei Siciliani Indignati'', USI),<ref>http://siciliainformazioni.com/redazione/670149/amao-e-il-suo-movimento-nazionale-siciliano-scendono-in-campo-per-il-centrodestra</ref><ref>http://formiche.net/blog/2017/08/20/armao-sicilia-berlusconi</ref><ref>http://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2017-08-22/armao-leader-indignati-che-indigna-parte-forza-italia-134041.shtml</ref> received the support of [[Silvio Berlusconi]] and [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] (FI),<ref>http://www.lastampa.it/2017/08/26/italia/politica/sicilia-berlusconi-decide-da-solo-punto-su-armao-e-sfido-gli-alleati-OAV1T39RcqEfVjdKjcQyVO/pagina.html</ref><ref>https://www.lecodelsud.it/berlusconi-armao-piu-un-colpo-fulmine-musumeci-non-indietreggia</ref> and was selected as candidate for Vice President, in ticket with candidate for President [[Nello Musumeci]], representing a broad centre-right coalition, notably including FI, [[Brothers of Italy]], [[Us with Salvini]], the [[Party of Sicilians]] and the [[Union of the Centre (2002)|Union of the Centre]].<ref>http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/sicilia-centrodestra-si-compatta-attorno-candidatura-1436499.html</ref><ref>http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/centrodestra-unito-sicilia-c-libera-musumeci-1436561.html</ref><ref>http://www.corriere.it/politica/17_settembre_02/sicilia-berlusconi-scendo-campo-io-ok-ticket-musumeci-armao-45a10d06-8fe2-11e7-90ab-5e72a21f32c7.shtml</ref><ref>http://palermo.repubblica.it/politica/2017/09/02/news/regionali_berlusconi_in_campo_per_la_sicilia_modlelo_da_esportare_alle_politiche_-174455918</ref>
After the election, in which the MNS did not field own lists, and Musumeci's election as President, Armao was sworn in as Vice President and minister of Economy.<ref>http://gds.it/2017/11/29/regione-ecco-la-nuova-giunta-nomi-e-foto_761900</ref>
